Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Reserve a couple of @thyme{1/4%ounce} sprigs for the next step. Strip leaves from remaining stems until you have 1 tsp (2 tsp for 4); mince leaves. Trim, peel, and cut @parsnip{6%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Halve, core, and slice @apple{1}(halved, cored and sliced into ½-inch-thick wedges). Halve, peel, and cut half the @red onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges (whole onion for 4). Mince @parsley{1/4%ounce}.

== Pilaf ==

In a #small pot{}, combine @bulgur wheat{1/2%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, reserved thyme sprigs, @water{1%cup}, half the @smoky cinnamon paprika spice{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest in the next step), @salt{1/2%tsp}, and a pinch of @pepper{}. (For 4 servings, use 2 cups water and 1 tsp salt.)

Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until water has absorbed and bulgur is tender, ~{12-15%minutes}. Keep covered off heat.

While bulgur cooks, toss parsnip, apple, and onion on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, minced thyme, remaining cinnamon paprika spice, and a big pinch of salt and pepper. (For 4 servings, divide between two sheets; roast on top and middle racks.)

Roast on top rack for ~{5%minutes}, then remove sheet from oven. Carefully add @Italian pork sausage{9%ounce} to same sheet. (For 4, divide sausage between both sheets; once added, swap rack positions halfway through remaining roasting time.)

Return to oven until sausage is cooked through and veggies are browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes} more.

== Lemon Pepper Sauce ==

Meanwhile, zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lemon juice, a pinch of lemon zest, and a big pinch of pepper. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt.

== To Serve ==

Once everything is done roasting, carefully transfer sausage to a #cutting board{} to rest.

Transfer parsnip, apple, onion, and any juices on sheet to a #large bowl{}. TIP: Those roasty juices add so much flavor to the dish.

Add bulgur, half the parsley, remaining lemon zest, a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, and a couple big squeezes of lemon juice. Stir gently to combine. Season with salt and pepper.

Thinly slice sausage on a diagonal.

Divide bulgur mixture between plates and top with sliced sausage. Drizzle with sauce and sprinkle with remaining parsley. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.